            	<p>One of the key agenda items at this year's Two Sessions is the review and approval of the city's first regulations on domestic garbage management. It clarifies how to discard, collect, transport and process domestic garbage in a categorized manner, and designates who is responsible for each step. </p>
                 <div class="section-title text-center wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s" style="margin-top:60px;">
                        <h2>Categorization</h2>
                        <span class="title-underline wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" data-wow-duration="1s"><i class="fa fa-circle"></i></span>
                    </div>
			</div>
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" style="border-bottom:solid 1px #ddd;">
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-push-6 wow fadeInRight" data-wow-duration="1s">
				<div class="feat-one-img">
					<img src="img/about/pix-dangerous.jpg" class="img-responsive">
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-6 col-md-pull-6 wow fadeInLeft" data-wow-duration="1s">
				<div class="feat-one-text">
					<p><strong>Hazardous garbage</strong> includes batteries, fluorescent lamp tubes, expired medicines, as well as paint and paint containers. This group poses health or environmental threats.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
            </div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" style="border-bottom:solid 1px #ddd;">
