<section class="feat-two">
    	<div class="container">
        	<div class="row">
            <div class="session-about col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
            <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:90px;"><img src="img/figure-g.png" style="width:60%;"/></div>
                 <div class="section-title text-center wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s">
                        <h2>Source Reduction</h2>
                        <span class="title-underline wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" data-wow-duration="1s"><i class="fa fa-circle"></i></span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Reducing the source of garbage is an effective way to lower the total amount of garbage a city generates. This demands a joint effort on behalf of different industries, from hotels and restaurants to factories and offices.</p>
			</div>
            </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="about" class="about">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
        
			<div class="mobile-features">
                   
				<!-- Start Mobile Slider -->
				<div class="col-md-2">
					<div class="features-slider owl-carousel owl-theme wow fadeInLeft" data-wow-duration="1s">
						<div class="item"></div><div class="item"></div><div class="item"></div><div class="item"></div><div class="item"></div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<!-- End Mobile Slider -->
				<!-- Start Mobile Slider Content -->
				<div class="col-md-8">
					<!-- Start Slider Links -->
					<ul class="nav nav-pills nav-stacked">
						<li class="space active-icon" data-owl-item="0" style="background:url(img/ic_gp1.png) no-repeat;"></li>
						<li class="space" data-owl-item="1" style="background:url(img/ic_gp2.png) no-repeat;"></li>
						<li class="space" data-owl-item="2" style="background:url(img/ic_gp3.png) no-repeat;"></li>
						<li class="space" data-owl-item="3" style="background:url(img/ic_gp4.png) no-repeat;"></li>
						<li class="space" data-owl-item="4" style="background:url(img/ic_gp5.png) no-repeat;"></li>
					</ul>
					<!-- End Slider Links -->
					<div class="tab-content">
						<!-- Start Single One -->
						<div class="tab-pane active" id="tab_a" data-owl-item="0">
							<h4>Green Manufacturing</h4>
							<p>Factories and companies should try to use recyclable and degradable materials, clean production techniques and equipment that emits less pollutants.</p>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single One -->
						<!-- Start Single One -->
						<div class="tab-pane" id="tab_b" data-owl-item="1">
							<h4>Green Office Work</h4>
							<p>Government departments and enterprises should use more recycled paper and less disposable stationery. No disposable cups are allowed inside government office buildings.</p>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single One -->
						<!-- Start Single One -->
						<div class="tab-pane" id="tab_c" data-owl-item="2">
							<h4>Green Consumption</h4>
							<p>Hotels are not allowed to provide disposable items like slippers and shower caps if not requested by guests. Restaurant owners and takeaway operators can no longer provide disposable chopsticks and spoons. Failing to abide by these new rules could lead to fines ranging from 500 to 5,000 yuan.</p>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single One -->
						<!-- Start Single One -->
						<div class="tab-pane" id="tab_d" data-owl-item="3">
							<h4>Green Wet Market</h4>
							<p>New wet markets must install equipment to process wet garbage. Failing to do so could lead to fines of 5,000 to 50,000 yuan. Stricter management will be adopted of agricultural markets, wet markets, supermarkets and fruit and vegetable production centers to reduce wet garbage from the source.</p>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single One -->
						<!-- Start Single One -->
						<div class="tab-pane" id="tab_e" data-owl-item="4">
							<h4>Green Packaging</h4>
							<p>Companies should not overpackage their products. Couriers should use electronic receipts, recyclable bags, boxes and adhesive tapes, and reduce the size of packaging. E-commerce retailers are encouraged to provide options for green packaging and give discounts and bonuses to customers who make such choices.</p>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single One -->
						<!-- Start Single One -->
					</div>
					<!-- End tab content -->
				</div>
				<!-- End Mobile Slider Content -->
			</div>
			<!-- End mobile-features -->
		</div>
		<!-- End row -->
	</div>
	<!-- End Container -->
</section>
<!-- End About -->
<section class="feat-three">
    	<div class="container">
        	<div class="row">
            <div class="session-about col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
                 <div class="section-title text-center wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s">
                       <h2>The Administrator</h2>
                        <span class="title-underline wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" data-wow-duration="1s"><i class="fa fa-circle"></i></span>
                    </div>
                   <p>Now we know that we can't throw garbage away the way we used to, but who’s going to monitor what we do? The regulations stipulate a role called "the Administrator," who will oversee almost everything related to garbage sorting.</p>
			</div>
            </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="features" class="features">
	<div class="container">
        <div class="row">
        	<h2 style="text-align:center;margin-top:-120px;">Who is the Administrator?</h2>
        </div>
		<div class="all-features">
			<div class="row">
			
				<!-- Start Left Features -->
				<div class="col-md-4 feat-width">
					<div class="feat-left wow fadeInRight" data-wow-duration="1s">
						<!-- Start Single Item -->
						<div class="single-feat first-feat">
							<div class="icon-place">
								<img src="img/ic_adm1.png" />
							</div>
							<div class="feat-text">
								<h4>Government organizations & enterprises</h4>
								<p>The Administrator is the property management company that oversees their office building. If there's none, it will be the owner of the building.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single Item -->
						<!-- Start Single Item -->
						<div class="single-feat">
							<div class="icon-place">
								<img src="img/ic_adm4.png" />
							</div>
							<div class="feat-text">
								<h4>Residential buildings & complexes</h4>
								<p>The Administrator is its property management company. If there’s no property management company, the Administrator is the owner of the building or complex.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single Item -->
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="col-md-4 feat-width">
					<div class="feat-center">
                    <img src="img/pix-administration.png" class="img-responsive">
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="col-md-4 feat-width">
					<div class="feat-right wow fadeInLeft" data-wow-duration="1s">
						<!-- Start Single Item -->
						<div class="single-feat first-feat">
							<div class="icon-place">
								<img src="img/ic_adm3.png" />
							</div>
							<div class="feat-text">
								<h4>Public places & venues</h4>
								<p>For public places like parks, squares, roads, airports, Metro stations, as well as cultural, sports and entertainment venues, the Administrator is the director operating these places.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single Item -->
						<!-- Start Single Item -->
						<div class="single-feat">
							<div class="icon-place">
								<img src="img/ic_adm2.png" />
							</div>
							<div class="feat-text">
								<h4>Exceptions</h4>
								<p>If the Administrator cannot be determined based on the previous rules, it should be appointed by the subdistrict government or township government that has jurisdiction over the area.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<!-- End Single Item -->

					</div>
				</div>
				<!-- End Right Features -->

			</div>
			<!-- End row -->
		</div>
		<!-- End all-features -->
         <div class="row">
        	<h2 style="text-align:center;margin:80px 0 20px 0;">What does the Administrator do?</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="row col-xs-12 col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2" style="font-size:15px;margin-top:20px;">
        	<p>1. Administrators need to place enough containers to collect the different types of garbage at the places they oversee. Failing to do so could lead to fines of 1,000 to 10,000 yuan.</p>
<p>2. If necessary, the Administrator needs to transfer domestic garbage, in a categorized manner, from where it is discarded to where it will be collected and transported. Failing to do so could lead to fines of 500 to 5,000 yuan.</p>
<p>3. The Administrator needs to provide guidance to residents on how to categorize their garbage. They can report to the subdistrict office if residents refuse to do so.</p>
        </div>
	</div>
	<!-- End Container -->
</section>

<section id="pricing-table" class="pricing-table">
	<div class="container">
		<!-- Start Section Title -->
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
				<div class="section-title text-center wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s">
					<h2>Collection, Transportation and Processing</h2>
					<span class="title-underline wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" data-wow-duration="1s"><i class="fa fa-circle"></i></span>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<!-- End Section Title -->
        <div class="row">
        	<div class="download-content col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
				<div class="text-download wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" data-wow-duration="1s">
					<p>Companies that are engaged in the collection, transportation and processing of domestic garbage should obtain a specific certificate that allows them to deal with the domestic garbage business. Each type of garbage is collected, transported and processed in its own way:</p>
				</div>
			</div>
        </div>
		<div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
			<!-- Start Single Price -->
			<div class="col-md-6 col-xs-12 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s">
				<div class="pricingTable">
					<div class="pricingTable-header">
				    	<img src="img/ic-g1.png" />
                    </div>
					<h3 class="heading">Hazardous garbage</h3>
					<div class="topic-content">
						is collected and transported on a monthly basis or upon appointment, and then processed in accordance with bio-safety guidelines, including high-temperature treatment or chemical decomposition.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<!-- End Single Price -->
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xs-12 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s">
				<div class="pricingTable">
					<div class="pricingTable-header">
				    	<img src="img/ic-g2.png" />
                    </div>
					<h3 class="heading">Recyclable garbage</h3>
					<div class="topic-content">
						is collected and transported on a regular basis or upon appointment, and then handed over to companies specializing in reusing and recycling garbage.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
        </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
        	<div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
            	<div class="col-md-6 col-xs-12 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s">
				<div class="pricingTable">
					<div class="pricingTable-header">
				    	<img src="img/ic-g3.png" />
                    </div>
					<h3 class="heading">Wet garbage</h3>
					<div class="topic-content">
						is collected and transported on a daily basis, and processed in accordance with bio-safety guidelines, including biochemical treatment to generate methane or serve as fertilizers.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
            
            	<div class="col-md-6 col-xs-12 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" data-wow-duration="1s">
				<div class="pricingTable">
					<div class="pricingTable-header">
				    	<img src="img/ic-g4.png" />
                    </div>
					<h3 class="heading">Dry garbage</h3>
					<div class="topic-content">
						is collected and transported on a regular basis, and is processed by burning or landfill.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
        	<div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
            	<p><em>A real-time monitoring system will be installed on each vehicle that transports domestic garbage. Clear signage should also be displayed outside the vehicle indicating the type of garbage it transports.</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
		<!-- End row -->
	</div>
	<!-- End container -->
</section>
<section id="download" class="download">
	<div class="overlay">
		<div class="container">
			<!-- Start Section Title -->
            <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
                <ul class="more-policy wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" data-wow-duration="1s">
                    <li>The government will also phase in a mechanism that charges a certain amount to those who generate garbage. The more garbage generated, the higher the fee will be.</li>
     				<li>The government shall provide various forms of enquiry service for individuals and companies to get familiar with the garbage categorization system.</li>
     				<li>Anyone can report behavior violating domestic garbage management regulations directly to the government or via citizen hotline 12345.</li>
     				<li>Individuals and companies who keep violating the regulations could leave a stain on their credibility record and face further punishment on top of fines.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
		</div>
		<!-- End container -->
	</div>
